---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Placeholder from '../components/Placeholder.astro';
import { SITE_URL, CANONICAL_DESCRIPTION, profilePageJsonLd } from '../data/site.js';

const title = 'About | F. Aamir Ali';
const description =
  'The full story: FleetBot (the student and staff builds), the AI & Innovation Club, and the Surrey Youth AI Summit, plus the honest lessons connecting them.';
---
<Base
  title={title}
  description={description}
  canonical="/about"
  ogImage="/og/about.png"
  jsonLd={profilePageJsonLd(`${SITE_URL}/about`)}
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap about-grid">
      <div class="about-left">
        <a class="back" href="/"><span aria-hidden="true">←</span> Back home</a>
        <h1 class="a-title">The <span class="serif">story.</span></h1>

        <!-- The canonical record — byte-identical to schema + llms.txt.
             Third person on purpose: this is the on-the-record summary;
             the story below it is mine. -->
        <div class="a-record">
          <div class="a-record-eyebrow eyebrow">On the record</div>
          <p class="a-record-text">{CANONICAL_DESCRIPTION}</p>
        </div>

        <p class="a-para">The long version starts with FleetBot, a chatbot I built solo to answer the questions my 1,500-student school asks every day. I launched it to students in January 2026, then rebuilt it for staff on a physical terminal in the front office by April. Getting it deployed taught me the real lesson: shipping the code is the easy half. Privacy objections, approvals, and whether anyone actually uses the thing make up the hard half.</p>
        <p class="a-para">FleetBot also showed me how few students actually knew how to build with these tools, so I founded the AI &amp; Innovation Club, where every meeting is hands-on and everyone leaves having shipped something that works. That work eventually grew into the Surrey Youth AI Summit, which I planned and executed with Yuvraj from Panorama Ridge: the first youth AI summit in Surrey, where about 70 students from 14 schools spent a single day building real AI for local businesses.</p>
        <p class="a-para">What I keep coming back to is where AI meets real institutions: how you actually get a tool approved, integrated, and used inside a place that already has its own way of doing things. That's the problem I want to keep working on.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="about-right">
        <Placeholder label="headshot.jpg" sub="real photo · coming soon" ratio="4 / 5" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .section { padding-top: 118px; }
  .about-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.15fr) minmax(0, 0.85fr); gap: 54px; align-items: start; }
  .back { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 12.5px; letter-spacing: 0.05em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--muted); text-decoration: none; margin-bottom: 30px; transition: color .2s ease; }
  .back:hover { color: var(--accent); }
  .a-title { font-size: clamp(40px, 5.4vw, 68px); font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.02em; line-height: 0.98; margin-bottom: 26px; }

  .a-record { border-top: 2px solid var(--ink); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); padding: 18px 2px 20px; margin-bottom: 26px; }
  .a-record-eyebrow { color: var(--accent); margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .a-record-text { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--ink); font-weight: 500; }

  .a-para { font-size: 16.5px; line-height: 1.68; color: var(--muted-2); margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .about-right { position: sticky; top: 110px; }
  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .about-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 34px; }
    .about-right { position: static; max-width: 100%; }
  }
  @media (max-width: 760px) {
    .section { padding-top: 94px; }
  }
</style>
